
## Requêtes http pour l'API MonSalon

### Auth (cookie HttpOnly)
Le backend définit un cookie `access_token` (HttpOnly) lors de `POST /api/auth/login` et `POST /api/auth/register`.
Pour les requêtes suivantes, assurez-vous que votre client HTTP conserve les cookies (cookie jar). En plus, un `Authorization: Bearer <token>` est accepté si nécessaire.

### Inscription

```bash
POST /api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}
```

### Connexion

```bash
POST /api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
```

### Créer un service (nécessite un token JWT)

```bash
POST /api/services
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Coupe Homme",
  "type": "Coupe",
  "amount": 25,
  "paymentMethod": "Espèces",
  "duration": 60,
  "serviceDate": "2024-01-15T14:30:00Z",
  "clientId": 1
}
```

### Ajouter un produit (nécessite un token JWT)

```bash
POST /api/products
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "Hair",
  "name": "Shampooing",
  "description": "Shampooing doux pour cheveux fins",
  "costPrice": 12.50,
	"sellingPrice": 12.50,
  "stockLevel": 50,
	"image": "image.jpeg",
	"lowStockAlert": 3
}
```

### Créer une vente (nécessite un token JWT)

```bash
POST /api/sales
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentMethod": "Carte",
  "userId": 1,
  "clientId": 1,
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": 1,
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 15.00
    }
  ]
}
```

### Rendez-vous (appointments): créer
```bash
POST /api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clientId": 1,
  "serviceId": 1,
  "date": "2026-04-01",
  "startTime": "10:30",
  "notes": "Premier rendez-vous"
}
```

### Rendez-vous (appointments): lister
```bash
GET /api/appointments
```

### Rendez-vous (appointments): confirmer (PENDING -> CONFIRMED)
```bash
PATCH /api/appointments/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CONFIRMED"
}
```

### Rendez-vous (appointments): terminer (CONFIRMED -> COMPLETED)
```bash
PATCH /api/appointments/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "COMPLETED"
}
```

### Rendez-vous (appointments): annuler (anytime -> CANCELLED)
```bash
PATCH /api/appointments/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CANCELLED"
}
```

### Catalogue (public — prestations actives)
```bash
GET /api/catalog/services
```

### Catalogue (gestion — toutes les lignes, JWT)
```bash
GET /api/catalog/services/manage
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

### Catalogue : créer une ligne
`multipart/form-data` — champs texte + fichier optionnel `image` (comme pour `/api/products`).

```bash
POST /api/catalog/services
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----abc

------abc
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="name"

Coupe femme
------abc
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="type"

Coupe
------abc
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="amount"

8000
------abc
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="duration"

45
------abc
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

Coupe et brushing
------abc
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="isActive"

true
------abc
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="photo.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

<binary>
------abc--
```

### Catalogue : modifier
Même principe multipart ; sans partie `image`, le fichier déjà enregistré est conservé.

```bash
PATCH /api/catalog/services/1
Authorization: Bearer <token>
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----abc

(champs name, type, amount, duration, description, isActive selon besoin)
```

### Catalogue : supprimer
```bash
DELETE /api/catalog/services/1
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```
